<node id="CSCE 670 Web Search Learning Outcome">
  <data key="d0">CSCE 670 Web Search Learning Outcome</data>
  <data key="d1">learningoutcome</data>
  <data key="d2">Upon completion of CSCE 670, learners will be able to define and explain key concepts and models relevant to web search, including text indexing, retrieval models, evaluation, Web crawling, link-based algorithms like PageRank, and learning to rank.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-97b761a3d4ccc38fabdc762f72330b3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774749492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CSCE 670 Recommender Systems Learning Outcome">
  <data key="d0">CSCE 670 Recommender Systems Learning Outcome</data>
  <data key="d1">learningoutcome</data>
  <data key="d2">Upon completion of CSCE 670, learners will be able to define and explain key concepts and models relevant to recommender systems, including collaborative filtering, matrix factorization, recommender system evaluation, and implicit recommendation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-97b761a3d4ccc38fabdc762f72330b3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774749492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CSCE 670 System Design Learning Outcome">
  <data key="d0">CSCE 670 System Design Learning Outcome</data>
  <data key="d1">learningoutcome</data>
  <data key="d2">Upon completion of CSCE 670, learners will be able to design, implement, and evaluate the core algorithms underlying a fully functional web search system and recommendation system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-97b761a3d4ccc38fabdc762f72330b3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774749492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CSCE 670 Research Application Learning Outcome">
  <data key="d0">CSCE 670 Research Application Learning Outcome</data>
  <data key="d1">learningoutcome</data>
  <data key="d2">Upon completion of CSCE 670, learners will be able to identify the salient features and apply recent research results in web search and recommender systems, including adversarial information retrieval and neural models of retrieval and recommendation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-97b761a3d4ccc38fabdc762f72330b3b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774749492</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mining of Massive Datasets">
  <data key="d0">Mining of Massive Datasets</data>
  <data key="d1">textbook</data>
  <data key="d2">Mining of Massive Datasets is an optional textbook for CSCE 670, authored by Jure Leskovec, Anand Rajaraman, and Jeffrey D. Ullman, published in 2014, and available online.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-97b761a3d4ccc38fabdc762f72330b3b</data>
